This is generated with Jekyll
Jekyll sources live in the `source` branch

The theme I am using is too old and isn't compatible with the `github-pages` gem / `gh-pages` branch :(

Current work flow:
- git checkout source
- bundle exec jekyll serve
- edit edit edit
- review
- commit changes to source
- cp -r _site ..
- git checkout -
- cp -r ../_site/* .
- commit to master (i.e. push website to live)


Prereqs:
- install ruby & gem (tested with 2.7 and 3.0)
- clone repo
- checkout source
- bundle install
- verify shit works with `bundle exec jekyll serve`
